IAM - Password Policy
Strong passowords = higher security for your account

In AWS, you can setup a password policy
1.) Minimum password length
2.) Require specific character types
a.) Upper case
b.) Lower case
c.) Numbers
d.) Non-alphanumeric

e.) Allow all IAM users to change their own passwords

f.) Require users to change their passowrds after some time (Password expiration)
g.) Prevent password reuse


Multi Factor Authentication
This can be used to protect root account and also IAM users

Users with password and MFA string token will have the account secured even if security credentials are stolen/lost

MFA security devices:
1.) Virtual MFA device:
a.) Google authenticator
b.) Authy (AWS Authenticator)

2.) Universal 2 factor auth
yubikey device to autheticate user.

support for multiple Iam users with a single key

3.) Hardware Key Fob MFA Device
a.) Gemalto (3 party)
b.) AWS US GOV CLOUD 
